WEBVTT

1
00:01:59.050 --> 00:02:01.610
- Good morrow. Lady Rhea.

2
00:01:59.050 --> 00:02:01.610
- Cousin.

3
00:02:01.720 --> 00:02:03.650
What's today's quarry? Rabbit?

4
00:02:04.150 --> 00:02:07.280
- Deer.

5
00:02:04.150 --> 00:02:07.280
- Oh. fine challenge.

6
00:02:07.390 --> 00:02:08.820
Care for some company?

7
00:02:08.920 --> 00:02:10.220
I'd rather ride alone.

8
00:02:12.630 --> 00:02:13.890
Good fortune to you.

9
00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:02.140
Husband.

10
00:03:07.680 --> 00:03:08.950
What brings you to the Vale?

11
00:03:13.520 --> 00:03:17.480
Or have you at last come

12
00:03:13.520 --> 00:03:17.480
to consummate our marriage?

13
00:03:19.030 --> 00:03:21.550
The Vale's sheep might be willing.

14
00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:23.130
even if I'm not.

15
00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:26.870
Our sheep are prettier. after all.

16
00:03:28.370 --> 00:03:32.070
Or perhaps your brother has at last

17
00:03:28.370 --> 00:03:32.070
had his fill of your company.

18
00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:36.080
Cast you aside

19
00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:36.080
in favor of a little girl.

20
00:03:42.250 --> 00:03:43.840
What will you do now?

21
00:03:44.820 --> 00:03:47.920
Will you strike the child down?

22
00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:49.320
Or?

23
00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:40.440
I knew you couldn't finish.

24
00:04:42.380 --> 00:04:43.570
Craven!

25
00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:24.920
Thank you.

26
00:06:06.530 --> 00:06:07.690
A moment.

27
00:06:15.140 --> 00:06:16.500
I do not wish to see you go.

28
00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:21.480
Such is the King's decision.

29
00:06:21.540 --> 00:06:23.310
A decision I most bitterly regret.

30
00:06:26.350 --> 00:06:28.340
And yet. you made it possible.

31
00:06:30.550 --> 00:06:32.040
You chose Rhaenyra.

32
00:06:33.520 --> 00:06:35.050
She swore her innocence.

33
00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:36.680
and I believed her.

34
00:06:36.760 --> 00:06:39.750
You wanted to believe her.

35
00:06:36.760 --> 00:06:39.750
as did her father.

36
00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:41.260
Your informant was wrong.

37
00:06:41.360 --> 00:06:44.200
An honest mistake. perhaps.

38
00:06:41.360 --> 00:06:44.200
but I did not foresee this!

39
00:06:44.270 --> 00:06:45.860
You should have.

40
00:06:45.930 --> 00:06:49.100
If you had not been so relentless

41
00:06:45.930 --> 00:06:49.100
in advancing Aegon as heir!

42
00:06:59.780 --> 00:07:01.080
Listen to me. daughter.

43
00:07:02.450 --> 00:07:04.510
The King will die.

44
00:07:04.590 --> 00:07:07.890
It may be months or years.

45
00:07:04.590 --> 00:07:07.890
but he'll not live to be an old man.

46
00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:09.930
And if Rhaenyra succeeds him.

47
00:07:10.030 --> 00:07:13.360
war will follow. do you understand?

48
00:07:13.430 --> 00:07:15.230
The realm will not accept her.

49
00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:16.790
And to secure her claim.

50
00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:19.560
she'll have to put

51
00:07:16.900 --> 00:07:19.560
your children to the sword.

52
00:07:19.630 --> 00:07:20.930
She'll have no choice.

53
00:07:23.940 --> 00:07:25.640
You know it.

54
00:07:25.740 --> 00:07:29.400
You're no fool.

55
00:07:25.740 --> 00:07:29.400
and yet you choose not to see it.

56
00:07:31.650 --> 00:07:33.770
The time is coming. Alicent.

57
00:07:35.250 --> 00:07:37.740
Either you prepare Aegon to rule.

58
00:07:37.820 --> 00:07:42.050
or you cleave to Rhaenyra

59
00:07:37.820 --> 00:07:42.050
and pray for her mercy.

60
00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:18.880
Where is Lord Corlys?

61
00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:18.880
He should be here to receive the King.

62
00:09:27.830 --> 00:09:29.160
Welcome to High Tide. Your Grace.

63
00:09:30.430 --> 00:09:32.660
What is the meaning of this. Lady Laena?

64
00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:35.430
Is this how House Velaryon

65
00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:35.430
greets its King?

66
00:09:36.570 --> 00:09:39.370
My father has but just returned

67
00:09:36.570 --> 00:09:39.370
from his long journey

68
00:09:40.110 --> 00:09:43.370
and he has hastened to the Hall of Nine

69
00:09:40.110 --> 00:09:43.370
to await Your Grace's arrival.

70
00:09:47.020 --> 00:09:48.950
Let's just get on with it.

71
00:09:58.590 --> 00:10:00.060
An outsider...

72
00:10:01.060 --> 00:10:02.360
among the natives.

73
00:10:03.600 --> 00:10:04.790
Lord Larys.

74
00:10:06.570 --> 00:10:07.970
Malvales.

75
00:10:08.470 --> 00:10:09.600
A rare bloom.

76
00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:13.600
Indigenous to Braavos.

77
00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:19.410
By all rights.

78
00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:19.410
it shouldn't be thriving here.

79
00:10:20.280 --> 00:10:23.050
Nature. such mystery.

80
00:10:24.390 --> 00:10:26.290
- The weather has been lovely.

81
00:10:24.390 --> 00:10:26.290
Indeed.

82
00:10:26.390 --> 00:10:28.220
And yet it is a dark day for the realm.

83
00:10:32.330 --> 00:10:33.590
Your father was a good man.

84
00:10:36.300 --> 00:10:37.790
As is yours who took his place.

85
00:10:41.770 --> 00:10:42.960
Yet still.

86
00:10:43.610 --> 00:10:46.230
the manner of your father's departure...

87
00:10:47.510 --> 00:10:50.100
it feels something of an injustice.

88
00:10:51.910 --> 00:10:54.080
What do you know of the matter

89
00:10:51.910 --> 00:10:54.080
of his leaving?

90
00:10:54.150 --> 00:10:55.850
When one is never invited to speak.

91
00:10:55.950 --> 00:10:59.680
one learns instead to... observe.

92
00:11:01.990 --> 00:11:03.580
You're perhaps in need of an ally?

93
00:11:04.630 --> 00:11:05.820
I'm the Queen.

94
00:11:05.930 --> 00:11:08.330
- I have no shortage of allies.

95
00:11:05.930 --> 00:11:08.330
Naturally.

96
00:11:08.430 --> 00:11:10.420
Princess Rhaenyra. for example.

97
00:11:11.830 --> 00:11:13.460
State your purpose. my lord.

98
00:11:15.940 --> 00:11:17.130
Um...

99
00:11:17.210 --> 00:11:20.200
I did wonder if she could be relied upon

100
00:11:20.310 --> 00:11:22.940
now that she is unwell.

101
00:11:24.380 --> 00:11:27.470
Unwell? I haven't heard anything.

102
00:11:28.220 --> 00:11:30.280
Begging your pardon.

103
00:11:28.220 --> 00:11:30.280
Your Grace. I may be mistaken.

104
00:11:31.950 --> 00:11:34.550
It's just that on the very same night

105
00:11:31.950 --> 00:11:34.550
your father was dismissed.

106
00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:38.290
the Grand Maester delivered a tea

107
00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:38.290
to the Princess's chambers.

108
00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:42.390
- A tea?

109
00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:42.390
Yes.

110
00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:47.400
That the Grand Maester himself brought?

111
00:11:47.500 --> 00:11:50.700
At the direction of the King.

112
00:11:47.500 --> 00:11:50.700
as I understand it.

113
00:11:53.470 --> 00:11:55.670
I do hope she's not unwell.

114
00:11:57.180 --> 00:11:59.340
Rhaenyra sailed

115
00:11:57.180 --> 00:11:59.340
with the King to Driftmark

116
00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:01.850
- yesterday at daybreak.

117
00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:01.850
Oh. what good news.

118
00:12:02.520 --> 00:12:03.710
I must've been in error.

119
00:12:05.320 --> 00:12:07.260
Ah. a relief.

120
00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:11.350
I thought for Mellos himself. well...

121
00:12:12.990 --> 00:12:14.990
her condition must be

122
00:12:12.990 --> 00:12:14.990
something very serious.

123
00:12:16.230 --> 00:12:19.220
What happiness it is to have been wrong.

124
00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:51.230
I'm sorry.

125
00:12:51.300 --> 00:12:52.630
Come. cousin.

126
00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:55.360
Let us discover what might be had

127
00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:55.360
for breakfast.

128
00:13:28.770 --> 00:13:30.170
Your Grace.

129
00:13:45.120 --> 00:13:47.110
Rise. Lord Corlys.

130
00:13:48.590 --> 00:13:49.850
Be welcome.

131
00:13:49.960 --> 00:13:51.590
- May I offer you a chair?

132
00:13:53.430 --> 00:13:54.490
Cousin!

133
00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:57.260
Princess.

134
00:14:04.870 --> 00:14:07.100
- Are you well?

135
00:14:04.870 --> 00:14:07.100
- Very.

136
00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:10.270
I congratulate you.

137
00:14:08.280 --> 00:14:10.270
Lord Lyonel.

138
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:13.540
I can think of no man more suited to be

139
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:13.540
the Hand of the King.

140
00:14:13.650 --> 00:14:16.350
That is very kind of you to say.

141
00:14:13.650 --> 00:14:16.350
Lord Corlys.

142
00:14:16.450 --> 00:14:18.440
His Grace has honored me with the post.

143
00:14:20.820 --> 00:14:22.150
Pity about Ser Otto.

144
00:14:24.690 --> 00:14:27.990
Despite spending most of my days

145
00:14:24.690 --> 00:14:27.990
amidst the grandeur of the Red Keep.

146
00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:30.960
the halls of High Tide

147
00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:30.960
never fail to impress.

148
00:14:31.030 --> 00:14:32.690
You flatter me. Your Grace.

149
00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:36.360
Though I do wish we could meet

150
00:14:33.700 --> 00:14:36.360
under happier pretenses.

151
00:14:37.910 --> 00:14:40.370
- How so?

152
00:14:37.910 --> 00:14:40.370
Daemon's wife.

153
00:14:40.480 --> 00:14:42.570
the Lady Rhea Royce. has passed.

154
00:14:43.580 --> 00:14:44.810
A hunting mishap.

155
00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:48.010
She was thrown from her horse.

156
00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:51.180
Her neck and skull

157
00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:51.180
both crushed in the fall.

158
00:14:51.250 --> 00:14:53.520
A most surprising end.

159
00:14:53.590 --> 00:14:57.920
Lady Rhea's skill as both

160
00:14:53.590 --> 00:14:57.920
rider and hunter were well-known.

161
00:14:58.030 --> 00:15:00.260
The gods are cruel.

162
00:14:58.030 --> 00:15:00.260
- Indeed.

163
00:15:01.160 --> 00:15:06.430
Lady Rhea was a fine woman

164
00:15:01.160 --> 00:15:06.430
and a good wife to my brother.

165
00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:10.370
Sad thing that she and Daemon

166
00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:10.370
have no heirs to succeed her.

167
00:15:10.440 --> 00:15:12.170
She stood to inherit Runestone.

168
00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:16.510
Mayhaps we can turn toward

169
00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:16.510
happier pursuits.

170
00:15:17.350 --> 00:15:20.010
- No. thank you.

171
00:15:17.350 --> 00:15:20.010
- What did you have in mind. Your Grace?

172
00:15:23.850 --> 00:15:27.190
I wish to propose a marriage

173
00:15:23.850 --> 00:15:27.190
between your son. Ser Laenor...

174
00:15:28.120 --> 00:15:31.020
and my daughter and heir.

175
00:15:28.120 --> 00:15:31.020
the Princess Rhaenyra.

176
00:15:31.090 --> 00:15:34.550
It's long past time our houses

177
00:15:31.090 --> 00:15:34.550
were united in blood.

178
00:15:34.630 --> 00:15:36.860
The last pillars of Old Valyria.

179
00:15:37.730 --> 00:15:41.290
You honor both me

180
00:15:37.730 --> 00:15:41.290
and my house. Your Grace.

181
00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:44.570
There are certain details

182
00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:44.570
I would wish clarified

183
00:15:44.640 --> 00:15:47.870
before the Princess Rhaenys

184
00:15:44.640 --> 00:15:47.870
and I could accept this most...

185
00:15:48.580 --> 00:15:50.200
generous proposal.

186
00:15:51.880 --> 00:15:53.470
What details?

187
00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:59.910
We would like to know

188
00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:59.910
how the succession will be handled.

189
00:16:03.220 --> 00:16:05.460
Rhaenyra is my heir.

190
00:16:05.560 --> 00:16:08.760
Upon my death. my throne and my titles

191
00:16:05.560 --> 00:16:08.760
will pass to her.

192
00:16:08.830 --> 00:16:12.290
She and Ser Laenor's firstborn child.

193
00:16:08.830 --> 00:16:12.290
regardless of gender.

194
00:16:12.400 --> 00:16:15.000
will inherit the Iron Throne from her.

195
00:16:16.940 --> 00:16:22.070
Can I presume that.

196
00:16:16.940 --> 00:16:22.070
in keeping with Westerosi tradition...

197
00:16:23.140 --> 00:16:25.770
their children would take

198
00:16:23.140 --> 00:16:25.770
their father's name?

199
00:16:27.250 --> 00:16:30.620
That they would be born Velaryons?

200
00:16:30.690 --> 00:16:32.480
Surely. Lord Corlys.

201
00:16:32.590 --> 00:16:34.850
you are not proposing

202
00:16:32.590 --> 00:16:34.850
the Targaryen dynasty

203
00:16:34.960 --> 00:16:37.650
end with my daughter

204
00:16:34.960 --> 00:16:37.650
simply because she is a woman?

205
00:16:40.660 --> 00:16:43.290
I only seek clarity. Your Grace.

206
00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:49.630
Might I have a chair

207
00:16:48.040 --> 00:16:49.630
brought in for you?

208
00:16:49.700 --> 00:16:50.690
I do not--

209
00:16:50.810 --> 00:16:52.770
No. I do not require a chair.

210
00:16:55.310 --> 00:16:59.440
Upon their birth.

211
00:16:55.310 --> 00:16:59.440
Ser Laenor and Rhaenyra's children

212
00:16:59.510 --> 00:17:01.980
shall take their

213
00:16:59.510 --> 00:17:01.980
father's name. Velaryon...

214
00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:05.950
in keeping with our traditions.

215
00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:07.510
However.

216
00:17:07.620 --> 00:17:11.390
at such time when their firstborn

217
00:17:07.620 --> 00:17:11.390
ascends the Iron Throne.

218
00:17:11.490 --> 00:17:14.620
he or she will do so

219
00:17:11.490 --> 00:17:14.620
bearing the name Targaryen.

220
00:17:16.230 --> 00:17:20.500
Dragons will rule the Seven Kingdoms

221
00:17:16.230 --> 00:17:20.500
for the next hundred years.

222
00:17:20.570 --> 00:17:22.560
just as they did the last.

223
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:37.680
This is an equitable compromise.

224
00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:40.550
Good.

225
00:17:41.420 --> 00:17:44.050
Now. if there's nothing further.

226
00:17:54.340 --> 00:17:58.670
In truth. if it had

227
00:17:54.340 --> 00:17:58.670
to be someone. I'm glad it is you.

228
00:18:01.040 --> 00:18:03.670
I know this union is not

229
00:18:01.040 --> 00:18:03.670
what you would choose.

230
00:18:04.910 --> 00:18:07.110
I hold nothing against you. cousin.

231
00:18:08.180 --> 00:18:09.580
No. I--

232
00:18:11.420 --> 00:18:12.610
Rather...

233
00:18:13.520 --> 00:18:16.120
Dare I say it is a matter of taste?

234
00:18:20.060 --> 00:18:23.050
I prefer roast duck to goose.

235
00:18:23.860 --> 00:18:25.460
I cannot say why.

236
00:18:29.040 --> 00:18:30.470
It's not for a lack of trying.

237
00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:34.270
There are those

238
00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:34.270
who like goose very well.

239
00:18:36.040 --> 00:18:38.410
I find it a bit greasy for my taste.

240
00:18:42.750 --> 00:18:45.120
I know that whatever agreement

241
00:18:42.750 --> 00:18:45.120
being struck up there

242
00:18:45.220 --> 00:18:47.150
will not change your appetites.

243
00:18:47.660 --> 00:18:49.650
nor will it change mine.

244
00:18:51.730 --> 00:18:52.750
And what do you propose?

245
00:18:59.130 --> 00:19:03.160
That we perform our duty to our fathers

246
00:18:59.130 --> 00:19:03.160
and to the realm

247
00:19:03.270 --> 00:19:05.430
and when it's done...

248
00:19:05.510 --> 00:19:07.940
each of us dines as we see fit.

249
00:19:18.590 --> 00:19:22.180
Viserys has taken

250
00:19:18.590 --> 00:19:22.180
to bed while his ship is readied.

251
00:19:24.660 --> 00:19:25.990
Perhaps I...

252
00:19:26.960 --> 00:19:28.360
overextended myself?

253
00:19:30.870 --> 00:19:32.300
Pushed him too close to the edge?

254
00:19:32.370 --> 00:19:35.170
My cousin chose to sail

255
00:19:32.370 --> 00:19:35.170
into this tempest. husband.

256
00:19:37.040 --> 00:19:39.510
It was undignified of the King

257
00:19:37.040 --> 00:19:39.510
to drag himself here

258
00:19:39.610 --> 00:19:41.940
and beg for Laenor's hand.

259
00:19:42.340 --> 00:19:43.540
Where is Laenor?

260
00:19:44.310 --> 00:19:46.780
He and Rhaenyra

261
00:19:44.310 --> 00:19:46.780
are walking the coast.

262
00:19:46.850 --> 00:19:47.840
Good.

263
00:19:48.650 --> 00:19:51.280
Do they seem... familiar?

264
00:19:52.050 --> 00:19:53.210
They grew up together.

265
00:19:54.490 --> 00:19:57.010
Familiarity is not at issue.

266
00:19:57.120 --> 00:20:00.150
I'm sure Laenor

267
00:19:57.120 --> 00:20:00.150
was already taken with her.

268
00:20:00.230 --> 00:20:02.160
She's grown quite comely

269
00:20:00.230 --> 00:20:02.160
these last few years.

270
00:20:02.230 --> 00:20:04.030
You know his true nature.

271
00:20:05.470 --> 00:20:06.460
He's still young.

272
00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:09.400
He will outgrow it.

273
00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:13.860
There is no pleasure

274
00:20:11.340 --> 00:20:13.860
in the world like...

275
00:20:16.010 --> 00:20:17.210
bedding a woman.

276
00:20:17.310 --> 00:20:20.180
We are placing our son in danger.

277
00:20:21.080 --> 00:20:23.380
The lords of the realm

278
00:20:21.080 --> 00:20:23.380
bent the knee to Rhaenyra

279
00:20:23.480 --> 00:20:24.680
and swore obeisance to her.

280
00:20:24.750 --> 00:20:26.580
That was before there

281
00:20:24.750 --> 00:20:26.580
was a true-born prince

282
00:20:26.690 --> 00:20:28.520
named Aegon Targaryen.

283
00:20:28.590 --> 00:20:30.750
Rhaenyra's succession

284
00:20:28.590 --> 00:20:30.750
will be challenged.

285
00:20:31.260 --> 00:20:35.090
Knives will come out for her.

286
00:20:31.260 --> 00:20:35.090
her husband. and for their heirs.

287
00:20:35.200 --> 00:20:39.030
Our house controls the realm's navy

288
00:20:35.200 --> 00:20:39.030
and half its dragons.

289
00:20:39.100 --> 00:20:41.330
